Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.48,0:00:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.52,0:00:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some highlights from the program:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.36,0:00:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we act\Nwhen our Christian neutrality is put to the test?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.36,0:00:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where \Nto draw the line between being
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.20,0:00:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a respectful observer\Nand an active participant?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.74,0:00:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Join this family as these questions come up.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.67,0:00:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re confronted\Nby the neutrality issue in all aspects of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.01,0:00:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What Bible principle should guide our thinking?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.52,0:00:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s music video focuses
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.52,0:00:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,on the unity among our brothers and sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.49,0:00:39.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As the world becomes more divided,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.99,0:00:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we become more united!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.63,0:00:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the March 2019 program \Nof JW Broadcasting!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.92,0:01:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin by traveling to the country of Armenia,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.15,0:01:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is located in the Caucasus
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.69,0:01:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—a region situated\Nat the border of Europe and Asia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.23,0:01:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite facing persecution for many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.96,0:01:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers and sisters in Armenia
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.07,0:01:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,have remained loyal to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The story of Armenia
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.11,0:01:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is a story of faith
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.64,0:01:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,—the faith\Nof courageous brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.85,0:01:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who endured mob violence,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.18,0:01:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,protests, and threats
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.52,0:01:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,from those who do not know God;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.12,0:01:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the faith of young brothers\Nwho were imprisoned
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.99,0:01:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,because they refused\Nto compromise their neutrality;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.40,0:01:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and the faith of lawyers
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.80,0:01:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,who defended them\Nwhen they were arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.70,0:02:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In the early part of this period,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.70,0:02:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the work operated out of an office\Nin a local brother’s home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.24,0:02:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the story is much different.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.15,0:02:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,On May 14, 2016,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.65,0:02:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers in Armenia\Nwere delighted to dedicate a group
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.19,0:02:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of new facilities\Nto accommodate future growth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.82,0:02:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—a branch facility
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.36,0:02:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,(mainly located on six floors\Nof a local building),
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.40,0:02:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,a new Assembly Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.41,0:02:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and also a school facility.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The dedication week\Nstarted off with a welcome night,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.91,0:02:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,where many\Ntraveled long distances to attend,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.28,0:02:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and some had not seen\Neach other for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.52,0:02:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’ve never been\Nto Armenia before,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.26,0:02:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and meeting the brothers\Nand sisters was such an experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave us a really warm welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.03,0:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was 90,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided, “No more Armenia.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And now I’m 96, and Jehovah said,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.30,0:03:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“You’re going to Armenia.”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.31,0:03:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blessing!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.28,0:03:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing to see so many brothers\Nand sisters from different countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.88,0:03:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and we enjoyed a very,\Nvery nice time with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.48,0:03:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to Jehovah, we really enjoyed this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.59,0:03:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But the spiritual gems\Nthat we all enjoyed the most
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.76,0:03:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,were during the dedication program\Nheld at the end of the week.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.60,0:03:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The program was filled\Nwith reports and interviews
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.47,0:03:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that touched our hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.17,0:03:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother Splane of the Governing Body\Ngave the dedication talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.01,0:03:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it your desire to dedicate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.91,0:03:52.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the branch facilities, the Assembly Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the school facility to Jehovah today?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We could never have imagined\Nsuch a thing happening five years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,From the time\Nthat we arrived at the airport
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and we saw\Nthe brothers boldly holding up
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.87,0:04:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the jw.org sign with their badges,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.70,0:04:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,we were just so overwhelmed\N—so moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.34,0:04:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And I could feel as if\NI’m in the Paradise today
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.98,0:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because we have so many guests\Nfrom different countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.08,0:04:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could see their happy faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.78,0:04:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,For many years, to be in courts
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.89,0:04:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—in legal battles for our brothers\Nas conscientious objectors
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.79,0:04:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or to go to the court
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.36,0:04:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for fighting a case\Nfor just one Kingdom Hall—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.56,0:04:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly to have a branch
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.03,0:04:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and Assembly Hall\Nand school facilities right away,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.87,0:04:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s for me kind of unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.64,0:04:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Today is a great day
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.31,0:04:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for Jehovah’s people in Armenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.25,0:05:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, Jehovah has seen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.35,0:05:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the faithful obedience\Nof our brothers and sisters in Armenia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.22,0:05:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We have witnessed Jehovah\N‘open the floodgates of the heavens
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.89,0:05:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,‘and actually empty out a blessing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.26,0:05:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,until there is no more want.’
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.73,0:05:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Our theme this month is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.17,0:05:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“Christian Neutrality
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“—What It Means, What It Takes,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.07,0:05:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and Why We Choose It.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.54,0:05:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your opinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.71,0:05:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you stand?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.88,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Can one person\Nmake a difference in countering injustice?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When we hear people\Ndiscussing political topics,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.42,0:05:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we might at first think\Ntheir conversation is purely philosophical;
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.52,0:05:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but when injustice threatens our loved ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.59,0:05:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it can seem personal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.16,0:05:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,We expect that people\Nwill be divided over political ideology.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Revelation chapters 8-13 \Nforetold that in the last days,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.57,0:05:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,government would be\Nthe burning issue among mankind
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.01,0:06:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that people\Nwould feel pressured to take sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The question each of us\Nneeds to ask himself is,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.75,0:06:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How do I respond when people\Ndebate solutions to serious injustices?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,As Christians,\Nwe’re most interested
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.79,0:06:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the example of Christ.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.53,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If ever there was a person who could make\Na difference in countering injustice,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.00,0:06:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it was Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.00,0:06:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He felt deep compassion for people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.94,0:06:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And with his abilities to feed the hungry,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.87,0:06:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,heal the sick, raise the dead,\Nand reach hearts with his winsome words,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.64,0:06:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus could have exerted\Ninvincible influence in the realm of politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.58,0:06:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He certainly had the opportunity to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.52,0:06:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan was pleased to offer him
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.52,0:06:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“all the kingdoms of the inhabited earth”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.52,0:06:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in an exchange for one act of worship.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.39,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jesus wouldn’t accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.56,0:06:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither did he assert that Satan\Nhad no authority to make such an offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.40,0:06:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, Jesus’ own countrymen\Ntried to make him king,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.14,0:07:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but he rejected that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.44,0:07:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Later still, someone asked him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it was lawful\Nto pay taxes to the Roman government.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.61,0:07:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Again, Jesus didn’t take sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.68,0:07:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,He refused to become a world ruler,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.12,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a national leader, or a political activist.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Did that mean that Jesus didn’t care?\Nthat he had no opinion?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.93,0:07:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,To the contrary!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.46,0:07:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus cared more deeply than we can fathom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.46,0:07:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And by treating people fairly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.47,0:07:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus promoted justice\Nat the most fundamental level.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, his principal focus
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.71,0:07:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was on teaching people\Nabout the Kingdom of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which would eliminate injustice for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.68,0:07:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what did Jesus\Nindicate should be our position
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.78,0:07:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,regarding human governments?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.05,0:07:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn from Jesus’ response\Nto the question about Roman taxation
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.69,0:07:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded at Mark 12:15-17:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Bring me a denarius to look at.’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“They brought one, and he said to them:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.50,0:08:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Whose image and inscription is this?’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.47,0:08:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“They said to him: ‘Caesar’s.’
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.54,0:08:12.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jesus then said:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.91,0:08:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Pay back Caesar’s things to Caesar,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.01,0:08:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but God’s things to God.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.68,0:08:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What are Caesar’s things?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.55,0:08:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At Romans 13:1-7,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.02,0:08:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the apostle Paul lists tax, tribute,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.49,0:08:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,fear, and honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.53,0:08:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice, too, that Jesus said\Nto “pay back Caesar’s things.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.53,0:08:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that imply?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.54,0:08:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That Caesar, \Nthe ruling authority of the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.94,0:08:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,had issued valuable things\N—coins, for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.94,0:08:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, Caesar had the right\Nto ask for some of those coins back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.81,0:08:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,This enabled the State\Nto continue rendering necessary services.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.88,0:08:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus acknowledged that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:08:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.69,0:09:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,our most valuable possessions\Nare grants from God himself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.26,0:09:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—such gifts as our heart,\Nour life, our mind, and our strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.26,0:09:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t give those things back to Caesar
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.10,0:09:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because Caesar\Ndidn’t grant them to us in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We rightly give those things back to God
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.54,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in the form of our dedication and our love.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Regarding our love for God,\NJesus said at Mark 12:30:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.72,0:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“You must love Jehovah your God
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“with your whole heart\Nand with your whole soul
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“and with your whole mind
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and with your whole strength.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.63,0:09:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So the love we give back to God is total
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.13,0:09:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,—no bodily part, function,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.44,0:09:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity, or desire being left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.74,0:09:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who love God take the side of Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,whom Jehovah has appointed as King.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:10:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But how would Jesus’ disciples\Ndefend his Kingdom when people opposed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.75,0:10:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We gain insight from events that occurred
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.49,0:10:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on the last night of Jesus’ life on earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.43,0:10:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Recall from Matthew chapter 26
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that when “a large crowd\Nwith swords and clubs” came to arrest Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.70,0:10:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter “drew his sword and struck\Nthe slave of the high priest, taking off his ear.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.61,0:10:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,John reports that the slave’s name was Malchus.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.18,0:10:30.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Luke adds that Jesus touched\Nthe man’s ear and healed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.18,0:10:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus bore no ill will\Ntoward the men taking him into custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.82,0:10:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Further, according to Matthew 26:52,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.62,0:10:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus told Peter:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.02,0:10:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Return your sword to its place,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.26,0:10:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“for all those who take up the sword
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.80,0:10:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,will perish by the sword.”
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.33,0:10:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did Jesus disapprove of Peter’s brave act?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.10,0:10:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For the same reason that he had avoided\Nthe political process all the way up to that point.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus explained this when he appeared\Nbefore Pontius Pilate later that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.72,0:11:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,At John 18:36, we read:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.69,0:11:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“My Kingdom is no part of this world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.89,0:11:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, because Jesus’ Kingdom\Nis not of human origin,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t need human defenses.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.83,0:11:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we be sure\Nthat this is what Jesus meant?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.30,0:11:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Look closely at the rest of John 18:36:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.74,0:11:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“If my Kingdom were part of this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.08,0:11:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“my attendants would have fought
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.35,0:11:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“that I should not be handed over to the Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.68,0:11:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as it is, my Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.15,0:11:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,is not from this source.”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So as Christians,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.96,0:11:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what is our position\Nwhere political matters are concerned?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.43,0:11:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We are neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.83,0:11:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people\Nmisunderstand this viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.50,0:12:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Some have concluded that because we\Ndon’t promote one human government,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.40,0:12:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that we must be promoting\Nanother human government.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.64,0:12:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the 1950’s,\Nin what is now the Republic of Congo,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.31,0:12:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,authorities falsely accused\NJehovah’s Witnesses of being Communists.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.55,0:12:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But during the 1970’s,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.55,0:12:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,when Congo adopted\Na Communist form of government,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.72,0:12:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the new authorities found fault\Nwith us for not being Communists!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.06,0:12:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, however, and for nearly three decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.56,0:12:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses have enjoyed\Nlegal status in the Republic of Congo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.96,0:12:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And whereas some have perceived
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.37,0:12:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,our Christian neutrality as sheer apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.77,0:12:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,others construe our position as a threat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.37,0:12:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s address both of these viewpoints.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.51,0:12:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First, there is a big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.11,0:12:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,between Christian neutrality and apathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.35,0:12:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Apathy is defined
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.35,0:12:52.99,Default,,0,0,0,,as “a lack of interest, enthusiasm, or concern.”
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.99,0:12:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We certainly don’t lack interest in people,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.26,0:12:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,nor are we insensitive to their feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.69,0:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Jesus,\Nwe strive to alleviate people’s suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,by helping them in practical ways
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.13,0:13:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,while teaching them about the only Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.97,0:13:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that can eliminate injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.20,0:13:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,By teaching people from God’s Word,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.71,0:13:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we endeavor to change hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.78,0:13:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,not political institutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.21,0:13:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We feel this approach is realistic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.28,0:13:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because mankind’s main problems\Nare not political
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.48,0:13:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,but moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.05,0:13:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But why can it be said\Nthat Jehovah’s Witnesses are not a threat
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.86,0:13:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather, an asset?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We conscientiously obey the laws,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.96,0:13:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we support our communities\Nthrough volunteer service
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.87,0:13:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or compulsory civilian service where that exists,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.70,0:13:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and we pay our taxes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.84,0:13:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, we don’t vote\Nfor political parties or candidates,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.01,0:13:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither do we disrupt elections
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.08,0:13:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,or interfere with those who choose to vote.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, we don’t lobby,\Ncampaign, or run for government office,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.82,0:13:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither do we criticize those in power,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.39,0:14:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,undermine their policies,\Nor demonstrate for political change.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.86,0:14:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, we won’t salute a flag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.43,0:14:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither will we burn a flag, spit on a flag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,or disparage the nation that a flag represents
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.50,0:14:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—even in lands where these are considered
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,protected expressions of freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.51,0:14:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true,\Nwe don’t sing national anthems,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.48,0:14:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither do we discourage\Nothers from singing,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.98,0:14:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,nor do we make\Na public spectacle of not singing;
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.05,0:14:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we simply don’t participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.42,0:14:31.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true, we wouldn’t kill people in war,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.09,0:14:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither would we attack people at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.02,0:14:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So while we don’t promote any political position,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.19,0:14:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,neither do we condemn any political position\N—even in our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.46,0:14:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That is what neutrality means.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.57,0:14:48.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t take sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.24,0:14:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if the demands of the State
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.74,0:14:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict with the commands of Jesus?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.48,0:14:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s a Bible principle for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.18,0:15:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you thinking \Nof what it says at Acts 5:28, 29
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.89,0:15:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—that “we must obey God\Nas ruler rather than men”?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.36,0:15:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not disregard for the State,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.29,0:15:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but, rather, reverence for God.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.06,0:15:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If the State demands\Nthat we do what God forbids
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.63,0:15:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,or refrain from doing what God commands,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.67,0:15:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,then we believe God\Nwould consider that an invalid request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.11,0:15:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, one might say,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.71,0:15:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,‘I can imagine some situations\Nwhere that viewpoint could get you into trouble.’
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.72,0:15:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus foretold as much at Matthew 24:9,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.59,0:15:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where he said:\N“You will be hated by all the nations
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.72,0:15:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,on account of my name.”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.03,0:15:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,More specifically, at Revelation 2:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.96,0:15:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said that some of his disciples\Nwould be thrown into prison
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.73,0:15:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,—not all of us but some.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.60,0:15:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’re not disappointed\Nif we don’t get thrown into prison,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.01,0:16:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but neither are we discouraged if we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.28,0:16:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our minds turn\Nto the thousands of brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.81,0:16:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,who have been sentenced\Nto prison over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.81,0:16:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,for their Christian neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.28,0:16:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We are proud of them.\NWe pray for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.59,0:16:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that Jehovah is pleased with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.49,0:16:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Their endurance under trial\Nspells victory for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.90,0:16:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How so?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.96,0:16:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,To the congregation in Ephesus, Paul wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“I ask you not to give up\Non account of my tribulations in your behalf,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.87,0:16:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,for these mean glory for you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.38,0:16:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote these words while he himself\Nwas under house arrest in Rome.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.18,0:16:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,In what sense did Paul’s tribulations
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.25,0:16:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“mean glory” for the Ephesians?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.16,0:16:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In that his perseverance\Nin ministering despite trials
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.79,0:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,showed the congregation\Nthat the privileges they enjoyed as Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.46,0:16:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,were of the highest importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.73,0:17:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If Paul had just given up,\Nwhat would that have implied?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.07,0:17:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That their faith, their ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.44,0:17:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and their hope in God’s Kingdom\Nwere not so valuable after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.31,0:17:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead,\NPaul’s endurance exalted Christianity.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.05,0:17:16.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It demonstrated\Nthat remaining faithful is worth any sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.05,0:17:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,In like manner, the endurance\Nof our dear brothers and sisters in prison
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.36,0:17:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,proves that their hope is alive
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.96,0:17:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the Kingdom they represent is real.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.63,0:17:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,They have an identity as envoys,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.47,0:17:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not of any human government,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but of the heavenly Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.34,0:17:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,—a Kingdom\Nthat will reward them with everlasting life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.14,0:17:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world without war.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.18,0:17:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether we face imprisonment or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.01,0:17:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,how prepared are we\Nto remain neutral in our day-to-day life?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.99,0:17:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, a Christian family discovers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.49,0:17:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that they need to spend more time\Nstudying about the subject of neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.33,0:18:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Collette, I’m home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.16,0:18:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the kitchen, Curtis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.63,0:18:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How was your day?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.63,0:18:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was a long day, but it’s nice being home.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.50,0:18:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,That smells amazing! I can’t wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.27,0:18:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, well, it will be ready in a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.94,0:18:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have a surprise;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.41,0:18:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,my job gave us tickets\Nto the game this weekend
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.31,0:18:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,—enough for all of us to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.01,0:18:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s downtown at the . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.68,0:18:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounded like fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.32,0:18:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a sport we could enjoy watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.72,0:18:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Collette and I hadn’t been in years,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.75,0:18:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don’t think the kids had ever gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.70,0:18:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We were all looking forward\Nto a family night out.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.17,0:18:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Dad, what exactly do we do\Nduring the national anthem?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, I wasn’t sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.94,0:18:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.18,0:18:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,would you please stand\Nfor the singing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.51,0:18:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of our national anthem?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.89,0:19:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, I have a question too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.19,0:19:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they salute the flag at my new school?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.70,0:19:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The conference\Nwith her teachers was next week,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.00,0:19:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we didn’t know what they’d do there.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.67,0:19:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, class.\NNow that everyone is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.50,0:19:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s all stand\Nfor the pledge of allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.58,0:19:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth, is everything all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.71,0:19:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think, Honey?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, tomorrow night\Nis our Family Worship evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.69,0:19:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So why don’t we do\Na study project as a family
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.43,0:19:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,on Christian neutrality at public events?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.19,0:19:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds like a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.83,0:19:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.83,0:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this will be great.\NWe’ll all get a chance to do our research.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.07,0:19:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked Daniel to research\NChristian principles on neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Collette and Elizabeth would find examples
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.51,0:19:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of ones who proved loyal under pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.55,0:20:04.85,Default,,0,0,0,,my job was to call Elizabeth’s new school
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.85,0:20:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,to find out if they saluted\Nthe flag or sang the anthem.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.19,0:20:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.23,0:20:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Mr. Johnson?\NThis is Curtis, Elizabeth’s dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d studied this topic\Nwhen the kids were younger,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but we needed reminders\Nfor these new challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.77,0:20:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The kids found some great information.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.31,0:20:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Several Bible principles applied.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.31,0:20:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But what Jesus said at Matthew 4:10
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.31,0:20:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was an essential foundation:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.88,0:20:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“It is Jehovah your God you must worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.59,0:20:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and it is to him alone\Nyou must render sacred service.”
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.29,0:20:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If we participate in a nationalistic ceremony,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.13,0:20:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re sharing in worship
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.00,0:20:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,of something or someone\Nother than Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But what would help us know what to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.67,0:20:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Elizabeth found\Nsome good examples to imitate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.14,0:21:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The account of Shadrach,\NMeshach, and Abednego
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.91,0:21:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,was one of our favorites.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.18,0:21:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,When King Nebuchadnezzar\Nordered them to worship the gold image,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.85,0:21:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they bravely stood\Nwhile others bowed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.95,0:21:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They were determined\Nto worship only Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.09,0:21:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and He rescued them from the furnace.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.16,0:21:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And there are modern-day examples
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.50,0:21:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of courage like the three Hebrews.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.87,0:21:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Some children have had to take a stand
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.44,0:21:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,when governments tried to force them
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.67,0:21:31.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to take part\Nin patriotic events during wartime,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.77,0:21:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,when feelings of national pride ran strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.31,0:21:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And despite legal victories\Nin some countries,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.45,0:21:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,young ones today are still put to the test.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.45,0:21:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned there was\Nno one answer on what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.46,0:21:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Situations are different\Ndepending on where we live
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.33,0:21:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,or what a person does\Nto show he’s participating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.36,0:21:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But in every case,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.90,0:21:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Christians in some way make it evident
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.37,0:22:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are respectful observers,\Nnot participants.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.64,0:22:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We felt good because we had decided
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.14,0:22:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what we would do\Nto be respectful but neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.88,0:22:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and show Jehovah\Nthat our family worships him alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.45,0:22:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the tests of our neutrality\Ndiffer depending on where we live,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.96,0:22:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,why not do what the family in the video did
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.82,0:22:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,—devote a Family Worship evening\Nor personal study session to researching
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.60,0:22:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,how to avoid participating inadvertently
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.30,0:22:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in any activity\Nthat would violate our Christian neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.37,0:22:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The subject of neutrality was highlighted\Nin a Watchtower article that we studied
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.54,0:22:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,in the congregations in 2016.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.08,0:22:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In this first episode of a new video series
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.62,0:22:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,called Lessons From the Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.32,0:22:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,note how our brothers and sisters have applied
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.92,0:22:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the admonition found\Nin that very practical article.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.34,0:23:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As a professor of finance,\NI need to be well-informed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.57,0:23:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,As a Christian,\NI also need to be well-informed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.34,0:23:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as do all Christians.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.34,0:23:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s difficult not to take sides in politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.28,0:23:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s very difficult\Nbecause we are aware of the issues.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.85,0:23:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I always really liked soccer\Never since I was little.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.89,0:23:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I lived in a poor area,\Nand soccer was what we used to do for fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.49,0:23:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a journalist\Nthat I liked to keep up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.20,0:23:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He would point out both the good\Nand the bad on all sides of politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.23,0:23:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he spoke up and pointed out\Nonly the bad side of a political party,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.74,0:23:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.71,0:23:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I live in the downtown area of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.04,0:23:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That is where\Nthe largest political demonstrations take place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.05,0:23:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,People from this area are really into politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.12,0:23:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They have definite opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.29,0:24:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though I always knew\Nthat we must remain neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.72,0:24:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I secretly approved of the demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.76,0:24:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,On the outside,\NI wasn’t jumping up and down or cheering,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.36,0:24:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but on the inside,\NI was saying: ‘Come on! Let’s win!’
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.97,0:24:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all about the desire, the crowd,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.81,0:24:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and the pride of your team\Nhaving the most victories or the most trophies.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to rationalize saying:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.28,0:24:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was created in Jehovah’s image,\Nand Jehovah is a just God.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.92,0:24:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What was speaking was my sense of justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.48,0:24:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought neutrality was shown through actions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.89,0:24:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and not through what I felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.22,0:24:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The April 2016 Watchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.09,0:24:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,has interesting information regarding neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.33,0:24:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Being neutral means that you\Ndo not consider yourself better than others
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.70,0:24:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because “in God’s sight, all people are equal.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.74,0:24:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,After studying the article,\NI realized that I needed to make changes;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.01,0:24:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not being neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.01,0:24:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So I read the article again.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.88,0:24:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I prayed to Jehovah;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.51,0:25:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I said to him that I knew\Nit was as if he were speaking to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.98,0:25:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The magazine really touched me deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.75,0:25:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember reading the article\Nat least three times that evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.96,0:25:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.96,0:25:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized how far off I was
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.83,0:25:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,from what God wanted me to be on the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.77,0:25:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The second situation mentioned in the article
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.37,0:25:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with news reports and the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.77,0:25:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The article even suggested that we limit
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.94,0:25:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,our intake of news\Nthat we watch related to politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.11,0:25:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There was another phrase\Nthat really moved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.28,0:25:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It said:\N‘Even if we don’t march with protesters,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.52,0:25:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,might we be with them in spirit?’
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.55,0:25:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I was with them. Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.82,0:25:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There were several phrases in that article
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.29,0:25:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that were written just for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.66,0:25:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When I cut back watching\Nso many news reports
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.80,0:25:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—and I had to—
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.56,0:25:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this helped me to have self-control\Nwhen I spoke to others at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.20,0:25:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When workmates mentioned\Nsomething that was in the news,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.34,0:25:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t have anything to say\Nsince I hadn’t seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.91,0:26:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.91,0:26:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,A workmate would say:\N“Did you see that so-and-so said this
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.21,0:26:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and that someone else made a statement?”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.42,0:26:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I would say:\N“No, I didn’t see it,”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.82,0:26:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the end of the conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.82,0:26:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The article mentions Romans 10:12
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.19,0:26:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,which says that Jehovah\Nis “Lord over all” of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.89,0:26:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘there is no difference\Nbetween Jew and Greek.’
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.26,0:26:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To Jehovah,\Nit’s not important if my country
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.90,0:26:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,has five or six titles\Nor if it won or lost the World Cup.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.77,0:26:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,To Jehovah, all people are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.61,0:26:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I took a piece of paper,\Njust a simple piece of paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.08,0:26:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wrote on it the four key points\Nthat the article talks about
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.11,0:26:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—four key points\Nthat will help us to remain neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.45,0:26:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep it in my purse;\Nthat way I can always read it at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.36,0:26:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I like watching soccer; it’s fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.13,0:26:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I still watch it on TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.43,0:26:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I still play soccer with my friends at Bethel,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.13,0:27:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’ve made an effort to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.60,0:27:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Little by little,\NI’ve managed to put soccer in its proper place.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.37,0:27:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps me to keep pride\Nand nationalism from getting the best of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.11,0:27:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I learned from this article\Nnot to express opinions about politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.55,0:27:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That has to come from deep inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.25,0:27:21.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If I’m convinced\Nthat God’s Kingdom is the best solution
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.39,0:27:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and that there’s nothing that comes even close,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.76,0:27:26.10,Default,,0,0,0,,remaining neutral will come naturally.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.09,0:27:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can’t let my guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.13,0:27:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I really enjoy studying\Narticles from The Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.00,0:27:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,especially those\Ndealing with practical matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.67,0:27:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They help me see the Bible as if it were\Na mirror that shows me where I can improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.64,0:27:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Following counsel
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.94,0:27:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and making the changes\Nsuggested in the article
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.95,0:27:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,has helped me to speak\Nwith the conviction
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.91,0:27:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that only the Kingdom\Ncan solve mankind’s problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.97,0:28:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our enemy Satan\Ntries to break our integrity in many subtle ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.97,0:28:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s important to know\Nahead of time how we’ll act.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.31,0:28:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Actions are important,\Nand yet they’re preceded by thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.25,0:28:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as one young brother discovered.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.45,0:28:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, note what Bible principle
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.29,0:28:27.33,Default,,0,0,0,,helped him to stay neutral in his heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.77,0:28:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“They are no part of the world.”\N—John 17:16.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.21,0:28:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“We must remain neutral\Nin order to be loyal subjects of God’s Kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.72,0:28:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“Otherwise,\Nhow could we have a clean conscience
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.72,0:28:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“when we preach the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.19,0:28:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“that only God’s Kingdom\Ncan solve mankind’s problems?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.45,0:29:01.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . As Satan’s system nears its end,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.79,0:29:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we can expect the issue of neutrality\Nto become more prominent.”
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.13,0:29:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,OK, people, we’re ready to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.20,0:29:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dawn, Jordan,\Ncan I get you to grab the blinds please?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.38,0:29:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,In your work groups this week,\Nyou’ll outline the policies
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.68,0:29:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you feel world governments should implement.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.19,0:29:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember, it’s young people like you,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.16,0:29:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,each of you, who must take action\Nto solve the problems that threaten our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.25,0:30:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,When war comes,\Nthey’ll look for you and me to do the fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.12,0:30:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you speak up and tell them,\N‘No, no, we won’t?’
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.24,0:30:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m more worried about the elections,\Nespecially for your generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.94,0:30:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who do you think is going to win?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.11,0:30:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Uhm, well, we believe that—
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.78,0:30:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,uhm . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.45,0:30:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s actually a very interesting question.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.82,0:30:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Jehovah’s Witnesses,\Nwe believe that it’s God’s Kingdom
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.05,0:30:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s going to bring about all the solutions\Nthat we need for all of our problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.22,0:30:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.22,0:30:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s £7.50, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.49,0:30:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.50,0:30:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, how can I help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.93,0:30:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, this new government policy
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.10,0:30:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,—I really think it’s going to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.50,0:30:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.77,0:31:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With their policies,\Nwe’ll be bankrupt within three years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.44,0:31:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it works, though,\Nit’s going to make people rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.24,0:31:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who are rich already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.51,0:31:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I’m fed up.\NThey say the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.67,0:31:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve invited a panel of experts\Nto explore these issues,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.17,0:31:30.27,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, can the opposition party win?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.27,0:31:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they keep their promises\Nto lower-income people?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.44,0:31:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And what changes could we expect\Non required military service?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.28,0:31:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll want to hear the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.31,0:31:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s begin by speaking to John McGarthy,\Nthe minister of education.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.78,0:31:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If put to the test,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I do want to take my stand for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.02,0:31:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But the outcome\Nof all these things can affect me now
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.66,0:31:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,—my family, my goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.30,0:31:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I stay neutral, even in my heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.04,0:32:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,John 17:14:
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.68,0:32:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have given your word to them, \Nbut the world has hated them,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.92,0:32:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“because they are no part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.15,0:32:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“just as I am no part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.89,0:32:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“I do not request\Nthat you take them out of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.32,0:32:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“but that you watch over them\Nbecause of the wicked one.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.23,0:32:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“They are no part of the world,\Njust as I am no part of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.33,0:32:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sanctify them by means of the truth;\Nyour word is truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.40,0:32:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Just as you sent me into the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“I also sent them into the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.67,0:32:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“And I am sanctifying myself in their behalf,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.04,0:32:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they also \Nmay be sanctified by means of truth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.12,0:32:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,No part of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.28,0:32:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,like Jesus,\Nboth in thought and action.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.06,0:33:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, but in our lifetime?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.26,0:33:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! And I have found something\Nthat has helped me to be sure of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.63,0:33:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I share it with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.53,0:33:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s here at Matthew 24:33.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.44,0:33:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus said: “Likewise also you,\Nwhen you see all these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.74,0:33:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,know that he is near at the doors.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.56,0:33:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our being neutral today is urgent
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.89,0:33:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah’s day is coming quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.76,0:33:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,On that day, we must be absolutely certain
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.10,0:33:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are on Jehovah’s side.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.57,0:33:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In this Bethel morning worship,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.67,0:33:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Anthony Morris of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.07,0:33:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,explains why we don’t need\Nto worry about the events to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.31,0:33:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, The Watchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.31,0:33:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,from where the comments are taken
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.85,0:33:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,had the theme
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.48,0:33:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Your Deliverance Is Getting Near.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.85,0:34:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was a sobering and yet
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.22,0:34:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,a very encouraging \NWatchtower study article,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.73,0:34:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and that theme \Nwas taken from Luke chapter 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.26,0:34:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you’d like to find that\N—Luke 21—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.00,0:34:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the context prior to verse 28,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.07,0:34:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,we know verse 26: \N“People will become faint out of fear
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.44,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“and expectation of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.61,0:34:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,coming upon the inhabited earth.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.61,0:34:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it mentions “the heavens . . . shaken,”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.12,0:34:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then, “see the Son of man.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.25,0:34:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And here’s where \Nwe find the theme, verse 28:
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.56,0:34:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as these things start to occur,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.46,0:34:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“stand up straight and lift up your heads,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.76,0:34:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because your deliverance is getting near.”
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.00,0:34:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as we know, \Nthis is fulfilled during the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.17,0:34:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s something to keep in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.88,0:35:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that at that time \Nwhen these events take place,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.05,0:35:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,they’ll be able to stand up
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.18,0:35:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and look forward to their deliverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.39,0:35:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, for a moment, just reflect back
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.06,0:35:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,on the Hezekiah video
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.16,0:35:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that we enjoyed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.26,0:35:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,during the convention season last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.10,0:35:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.10,0:35:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And what a beautiful job \Nthe brothers did in Audio/Video
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.54,0:35:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,depicting one angel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.01,0:35:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that destroyed 185,000 men.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.88,0:35:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It was spectacular!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.98,0:35:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,However, find Revelation chapter 17
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.79,0:35:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,—Revelation chapter 17—
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.99,0:35:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is what
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.89,0:35:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is foretold for the near future.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.36,0:35:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The context here at Revelation 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.20,0:35:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,where verse 12 mentions “the ten horns,”
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.80,0:35:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and then down into verse 13
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.87,0:36:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—after this “one hour with the wild beast”\N(the United Nations)—
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.08,0:36:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they give their “authority to the wild beast.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.28,0:36:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Humans in general \Nwould find that hard to believe
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.42,0:36:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when they look \Nat what’s going on in the world today.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.75,0:36:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s what they’re going to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.19,0:36:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 14:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.69,0:36:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“These will battle with the Lamb,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.03,0:36:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“but because he is Lord of lords \Nand King of kings,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.13,0:36:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“the Lamb will conquer them.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.93,0:36:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“Also, those with him
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.74,0:36:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,who are called and chosen \Nand faithful will do so.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.58,0:36:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.58,0:36:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as good as our brothers are in Audio/Video,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.45,0:36:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I personally doubt that anyone
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.48,0:36:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,could do a videography \Nand capture this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.36,0:36:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re talking about Christ Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.26,0:36:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the 144,000
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.93,0:36:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,anointed immortal spirit creatures,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and then Jesus has the holy angels
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.37,0:37:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that are under his direction as King.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.37,0:37:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,This is going to be spectacular!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.41,0:37:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, all things are possible with God,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.71,0:37:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think they’d have to have Him \Nto be able to show a video
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.28,0:37:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to capture what’s coming in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.02,0:37:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Just spectacular!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.02,0:37:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, just keep in mind \N(and The Watchtower made this clear),
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.76,0:37:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we don’t know the sure \Nand exact sequence of events
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.99,0:37:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,—the time order—\Nsome of it (as The Watchtower says)
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.86,0:37:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will likely overlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.13,0:37:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However, what we do know
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.90,0:37:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,—Jehovah has been kind about this—
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.54,0:37:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is what’s going to take place
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.64,0:37:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to start the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.08,0:37:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we find here in verse 15,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.31,0:37:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’ll read \Nthrough verse 17 of Revelation 17:
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.75,0:37:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“He said to me: ‘The waters that you saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.69,0:37:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘where the prostitute is sitting,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.75,0:37:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘mean peoples and crowds\Nand nations and tongues.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.26,0:37:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And the ten horns \Nthat you saw and the wild beast,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.83,0:38:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘these will hate the prostitute
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.13,0:38:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and will make her devastated and naked,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.17,0:38:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and they will eat up her flesh
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.44,0:38:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and completely burn her with fire.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.07,0:38:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here’s the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.81,0:38:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and verification for why this will happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.41,0:38:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,verse 17: “For God put it into their hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.98,0:38:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“to carry out his thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.38,0:38:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“yes, to carry out their one thought
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.95,0:38:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,“by giving their kingdom to the wild beast,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.56,0:38:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,until the words of God\Nwill have been accomplished.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.93,0:38:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s as good as done.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.66,0:38:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what’s going to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.66,0:38:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of how people view us
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.77,0:38:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when we preach this good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.47,0:38:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because this is good news\N—the destruction
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.47,0:38:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world empire of false religion,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.21,0:38:49.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the beginning of the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.58,0:38:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is spectacular news\Nfor God’s people,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.95,0:38:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and until it takes place,\Nthey won’t believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.35,0:39:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But it will happen because \NJehovah says it’s going to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.96,0:39:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’ll be a time for us \Nto prove our love for Jehovah God.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.56,0:39:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll be the only group protected by him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.30,0:39:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this was profound, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.30,0:39:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,this article in The Watchtower made this—
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.40,0:39:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought it was \Na profound statement when you think
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.10,0:39:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,about the organization we’re a part of.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.11,0:39:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It said in paragraph 9:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.11,0:39:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“This will not be the time to preach
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.68,0:39:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,the ‘good news of the Kingdom.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.95,0:39:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,My, we’re a preaching organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.25,0:39:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So there’s a time \Nwe’ll not preach the good news?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.76,0:39:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.36,0:39:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember one of our favorite verses?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.69,0:39:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s etched on the minds \Nand hearts of God’s people:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.90,0:39:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“And this good news \Nof the Kingdom will be preached
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.07,0:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in all the inhabited earth \Nfor a witness to all the nations.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.64,0:39:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don’t forget the last part:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.27,0:39:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“And then the end will come.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.64,0:40:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So during the great tribulation\N—no good news.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.65,0:40:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we do know there’ll be preaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.82,0:40:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think we’re unpopular now?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.82,0:40:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.69,0:40:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Revelation chapter 16,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.40,0:40:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the context \NArmageddon is being addressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.50,0:40:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice verse 21:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.37,0:40:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then great hailstones, \Neach about the weight of a talent,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.27,0:40:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,“fell from heaven on the people,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.64,0:40:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the people blasphemed God
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“because of the plague of [the] hail,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.75,0:40:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,for the plague was unusually great.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.28,0:40:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.62,0:40:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So the message and the preaching
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.89,0:40:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,are going to be like “hailstones.”
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.49,0:40:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know if you’ve \Never been in a hailstorm,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.79,0:40:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but this is a huge hailstorm
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.03,0:40:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,being depicted here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.03,0:40:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s likely, possibly, a hard-hitting message
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.10,0:41:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—maybe a declaration \Nannouncing that Satan’s world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.67,0:41:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is about to come to a complete end.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.18,0:41:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s just stay tuned.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.05,0:41:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And don’t feel bad—I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.95,0:41:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was out in the ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.95,0:41:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in one territory recently,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.06,0:41:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s good to suffer reproach.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.66,0:41:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We all need that, like Jesus did.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.93,0:41:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The door-to-door ministry \Nis good for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.70,0:41:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But see, if you think \Nwe’re suffering reproach now—
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.00,0:41:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.40,0:41:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just training for this future declaration
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.14,0:41:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ll have the privilege to share in.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.78,0:41:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, keep in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.78,0:41:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is this event that The Watchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.58,0:41:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,did mention in Matthew chapter 24.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.68,0:41:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you’ll find that,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.69,0:41:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s nice to have this clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.16,0:41:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew chapter 24,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.79,0:41:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re going to read verse 31:
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.43,0:42:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“And he will send out his angels
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.94,0:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“with a great trumpet sound,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.94,0:42:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they will gather \Nhis chosen ones together
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.51,0:42:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the four winds,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.88,0:42:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,from one extremity of the heavens \Nto their other extremity.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.38,0:42:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what The Watchtower stated there was
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.12,0:42:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that it’s not the initial gathering
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.12,0:42:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of the anointed nor the final sealing;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.35,0:42:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,this is when the remnant\N—the remaining ones—
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.46,0:42:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,receive their heavenly reward \Nduring the great tribulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.23,0:42:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And this event takes place at some point
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.66,0:42:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,after the beginning of the attack by Gog.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.34,0:42:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.34,0:42:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s when Matthew 13:43 is fulfilled:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.77,0:42:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“The righteous ones \Nwill shine as brightly as the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.61,0:42:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Kingdom of their Father.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.88,0:42:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So as we mentioned\N—sobering, yes, but encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.09,0:42:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes, so encouraging.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.35,0:42:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, let’s be confident;
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.12,0:42:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s trust in Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.13,0:43:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s no need to be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.33,0:43:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s keep up our spiritual routine
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.63,0:43:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and prove ourselves ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.80,0:43:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because the great tribulation is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.17,0:43:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jehovah’s day comes,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.31,0:43:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,our brotherhood will be safe because it’s united.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.51,0:43:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Our worldwide unity is but one of the blessings
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.95,0:43:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that result from our Christian neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.22,0:43:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s music video,\Nnotice the connection
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.62,0:43:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,between the love we enjoy as God’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.56,0:43:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and our being “no part of this world.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.06,0:43:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is entitled “We Are One.”
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.34,0:43:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s trouble in the world, disunity.\NNo matter where we live, no harmony.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.29,0:44:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,There are people suffering,\Nfighting for change.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.90,0:44:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But among God’s people,\Nwe trust in his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.10,0:44:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we must stick close to his Word\NAnd remain no part of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.15,0:44:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With love in ev’ry little thing we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.05,0:44:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Show love as we spread the good news,\NAnd feel the love of the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.60,0:44:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we stand out as diff’rent,\NWith Jehovah, we are one.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.81,0:45:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter where we go from sea to sea,\NWith God’s people, we find true family.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.06,0:45:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there are anxieties, but hope is real—\NA paradise to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.86,0:45:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,True peace is near.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.47,0:45:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So we keep trusting in his Word\NAnd remain no part of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.51,0:45:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,With love in ev’ry little thing we do.\NShow love as we spread the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.09,0:45:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And feel the love of the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.09,0:45:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we stand out as diff’rent,\NWith Jehovah, we are one.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.30,0:45:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We are one.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.07,0:46:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s stay faithful and endure\NAnd remain no part of this world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.78,0:46:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,With love in ev’ry little thing we do.\NShow love as we spread the good news,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.26,0:46:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And feel the love of the brotherhood.\NThough we stand out as diff’rent,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.10,0:46:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah,\NWe love in ev’ry little thing we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.15,0:46:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Show love as we spread the good news,\NAnd feel the love of the brotherhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.06,0:46:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we stand out as diff’rent,\NWith Jehovah, we are one.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.12,0:47:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The song was initially written\Nin the Lingala language,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.79,0:47:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,an African language spoken mainly
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.86,0:47:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Democratic Republic of Congo\Nand the Republic of Congo.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.73,0:47:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’d like to hear the song\Nin the Lingala language,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.56,0:47:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you can now find it\Non Video on Demand under the heading “Music.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.80,0:47:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,While you’re at it, why not listen
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.44,0:47:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to other original songs in different languages?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.41,0:47:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,After you have navigated to the “Music” section,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.41,0:47:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,change the language of the website
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.58,0:47:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the top right corner\Nto a language of your choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.29,0:47:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you noticed\Nthe many examples of Christian neutrality
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.45,0:47:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve seen during this program?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.12,0:47:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we visited Armenia and learned
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.63,0:48:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,how they’ve remained neutral\Ndespite persecution.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.80,0:48:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,After the talk, we learned the importance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.20,0:48:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of remaining neutral at public events.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.87,0:48:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we met a number of brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.04,0:48:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,who shared their experiences in applying
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.51,0:48:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Watchtower study article about neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.41,0:48:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Morris reminded us\Nof Jehovah’s protection
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.08,0:48:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when Jehovah judges this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.82,0:48:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And our music video encouraged us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.35,0:48:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to enjoy the blessings of unity
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.86,0:48:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that result from our Christian neutrality.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.73,0:48:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of the music video:
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.73,0:48:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice\Nhow our friends watched the broadcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.77,0:48:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and when the postcard came up\Nat the end of the program, they waved back?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.14,0:48:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt like doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.57,0:48:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, here’s another opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.84,0:48:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s visit our brothers \Nand sisters in South Korea.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.18,0:48:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Kingdom proclaimers arrived in Korea in 1912.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.19,0:49:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, the Republic of Korea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.55,0:49:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,has some 1,300 congregations
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.06,0:49:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,with over 100,000 publishers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.03,0:49:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Although the peninsula\Nwas under colonial rule for some time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.63,0:49:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and has been involved in other military conflicts,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.60,0:49:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s Witnesses there \Nhave maintained their Christian neutrality
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.77,0:49:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by not taking sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.57,0:49:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the last seven decades,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.78,0:49:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,more than 19,000 brothers\Nhave been imprisoned for their faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.68,0:49:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In 2018, a favorable court decision
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.98,0:49:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,was handed down\Nin behalf of these faithful brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.32,0:49:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the future, we look forward
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.89,0:49:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to even further relief\Nfrom fair-minded officials in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.46,0:49:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Ganseong Congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.07,0:49:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Their territory has a population\Nof approximately 23,000
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.84,0:49:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and is partially located
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.14,0:49:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,in the demilitarized zone\Nnear the North Korean border.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.11,0:49:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not uncommon for the almost 50 publishers
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.08,0:50:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to conduct over 60 Bible studies each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.52,0:50:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.75,0:50:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,some 30 publishers\N—or 60 percent of the congregation—
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.39,0:50:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,serve as regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.36,0:50:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of its location, many of the residents
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.03,0:50:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the villages in this area\Nare isolated from the rest of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.10,0:50:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.10,0:50:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,often meet people who work for the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.57,0:50:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the congregation’s proximity\Nto the border,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.81,0:50:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,busloads of tourists come on a regular basis
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.14,0:50:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the North Korean border.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.45,0:50:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To reach such visitors with the good news,\Nour brothers have organized
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.82,0:50:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,public witnessing stands\Nin a number of locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.45,0:50:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We love our brothers and sisters\Nin the Ganseong Congregation very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.93,0:50:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And they send their love\Nto all of us around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.93,0:50:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.07,0:51:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters\Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.
